# JARVIS-Style Futuristic GUI for Wednesday AI Assistant

Build a premium, futuristic JARVIS-like GUI using **PyQt6** with animated orb, glowing effects, chat panels, and full backend integration — without modifying any existing backend code.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Framework: PyQt6** — This plan uses PyQt6 for the GUI. It will be added to `requirements.txt`. PyQt6 supports `QPropertyAnimation`, `QGraphicsDropShadowEffect`, custom painting via `QPainter`, and native threading via `QThread`/signals/slots — all needed for a smooth 60fps JARVIS experience.

> [!WARNING]
> **Separate Entry Point** — The GUI launches from `gui/gui_main.py` (not `main.py`). The existing `main.py` CLI entry point remains untouched. The GUI re-uses the same backend functions (`process_command`, `speak`, `listen`, etc.) but drives them from the GUI thread model instead of the CLI loop.

