#### [NEW] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/Vishesh/Documents/AI%20Assitet/wednesday/gui/app.py)

Main window orchestration:

- **`WednesdayGUI(QMainWindow)`** — Main window
  - Layout: Central orb + status on top, chat panel in middle, input bar at bottom, side panel on right
  - Window: Frameless or dark-titled, fixed minimum size ~1000×700
  - Connects all signals/slots

- **`BackendWorker(QThread)`** — Runs AI processing off the main thread
  - `process(command)` → runs `process_command()` from `main.py`
  - Emits signals: `state_changed(str)`, `response_ready(str)`, `error(str)`
  - Intercepts `speak()` calls to emit text to GUI instead of (or in addition to) TTS

- **`ListenerWorker(QThread)`** — Runs voice listening
  - Calls `listen()` in a loop when voice mode is active
  - Emits `text_recognized(str)` signal

- **Signal flow**:
  1. User types command → `InputBar.command_submitted` → `BackendWorker.process`
  2. Worker emits `state_changed("thinking")` → `OrbWidget` transitions
  3. Worker emits `response_ready(text)` → `ChatPanel.add_message` + `state_changed("speaking")`
  4. After speaking → `state_changed("idle")`

